<div class="noprint plainlinksneverexpand navbar" style="background:none; padding:0; font-weight:normal;; font-size:xx-small;">This box: <a href="/wiki/Template:Discrimination_sidebar" title="Template:Discrimination sidebar"><span title="View this template" style="">view</span></a>&#160;•&#160;<a href="/wiki/Template_talk:Discrimination_sidebar" title="Template talk:Discrimination sidebar"><span title="Discussion about this template" style="">talk</span></a>&#160;•&#160;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:Discrimination_sidebar&amp;action=edit" class="external text" title="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:Discrimination_sidebar&amp;action=edit" rel="nofollow"><span title="Edit this template" style=";">edit</span></a></div>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p><b>Discrimination</b> toward or against a person or group is the treatment or consideration based on class or category rather than individual merit. It is usually associated with <a href="/wiki/Prejudice" title="Prejudice">prejudice</a>. It can be behavior promoting a certain group (e.g. <a href="/wiki/Affirmative_action" title="Affirmative action">affirmative action</a>), or it can be negative behavior directed <i>against</i> a certain group (e.g. <a href="/wiki/Redlining" title="Redlining">redlining</a>). The latter is the more common meaning.</p>
